<dl id="n06155o"> <dt class="nbunit"><a name="n06" href="#n06155o">N06 (VI.B.11)</a>:  <a href="../../FF/fnbs/n06all.htm#n06155o"> 155(o)</a></dt> <dd> <blockquote> manslayer flee to / cities of refuge <small>Red</small></blockquote> <dd class="well"> <ul class="list-inline" id="n06155o"><li>FW 62.11 </li><li><a href="../../flex/c/lexc.htm#n06155o">2010</a> </li><li><a href="../../flex/c/l39c.htm#n06155o">1939</a> </li><li><ms href="#n06155o">MS BL 47471b-10v</ms> </li><li>JJA 45:151 <a name="c20d" href="../../FF/fdra/cda.htm#c20d">Usage</a> </li><li> <a href="../../flex/c/c20d.htm#n06155o">Draft: I.3&sect;2.0</a></li> </ul> <blockquote class="sources">SIXTH COMMANDMENT. &ldquo;THOU SHALT DO NO MURDER.&rdquo;&mdash;This command forbids the taking away another&apos;s life wilfully. The Mosaic law punished the murderer with death; but <mark>the manslayer</mark>, he who by accident caused the death of another, <mark>was permitted to flee to one of the cities of refuge</mark>. <small> Anonymous, <a name="ATCC" href="../../FF/fdra/fdex.htm#ATCC"><cite title="source">Analysis of the Church Catechism</cite></a> (1879) 37</small></blockquote> </dd></dl>
